  "texts": [
    "To develop effective learning tools, educational research must keep pace with advancements, as effective learning necessitates the application of empirically validated theories from pedagogy, didactics, and educational psychology.",
    "Additionally, the simultaneous development of open-source platforms by both researchers and corporations is vital to ensure the economic viability of these technologies, prevent a digital divide, and offer equal opportunities for learners of diverse backgrounds.",
    "Such advancements could transform education by removing barriers like geographical constraints, limited interaction, language barriers, and the fear of asking questions, paving the way for a more personalized learning experience.",
    "While formative feedback has been widely studied in educational research, its application in advanced technologies such as artificial intelligence (AI) (specifically LLMs) is still in its early stages.",
    "The novelty of LLMs means that their potential to support SRL through feedback mechanisms is not yet fully recognized or explored."
